## Version 8.2.13

- better configuration for ALKIS exports, multiple exports possible
- implemented search for GeoJSON layers
- support for QGIS raster GetFeature responses
- added `isHidden` flag for model fields
- option `allowedServiceUids` for OWS services

## Version 8.2.12

- bugfixes and documentation

## Version 8.2.11

- support for styling of the layers panel in the client
- automatic redirect from http to https

## Version 8.2.10

- SLD support for raster layers
- added ALKIS option "gemarkungFilter"
- default spatial search tolerance set to 10px

## Version 8.2.9

- support for mbtiles layers
- added global and project-based variable support
- ability to import python modules in "expression" values

## Version 8.2.8

- optional composite rendering for QGIS layers
- text search categories

## Version 8.2.7

- OWS services futher improved and optimized
- [breaking] `metadata.attribution.title` renamed to `metadata.attribution`

## Version 8.2.6

- bugfixes in OWS services

## Version 8.2.5

- ALKIS indexing and export optimized
- ALKIS GeoJSON export
- standard-conforming CRS handling in GeoJSON

## Version 8.2.4

- support for SSL Postgres connections
- better support for geographic CRS in raster OGC services
- background jobs improved
- watch mode for the configtest command
- server configuration cleaned up
- framework for periodic tasks

## Version 8.2.3

- CSW service
- basic implementation of OGC filters
- use a dedicated namespace for the Client

## Version 8.2.2

- printing optimized
- new command `@pagebreak` in templates
- temporary files cleaned up
- docker image contains the exact git revision

## Version 8.2.1

- support for raster layers
- raster formats can be configured for all layers

## Version 8.2.0

- upgrade app image to ubuntu 24 and python 3.12
- built-in Mapserver added
